The paper deals with the problem of phase retrieval, which is a common problem in signal processing and imaging. The paper specifically focuses on the use of Frequency-Resolved Optical Gating (FROG) for signal reconstruction. FROG is a technique used in ultra-short laser pulse characterization and diffraction imaging, which are applications that fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
